The paper deals with the use of polar codes in a wireless communication scenario, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The paper also discusses the use of practical constraints on power and delay, which could fall under the categories of systems and control (cs.SY), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
